\subsection{Roleplaying a Fractal Warrior}

\begin{itemize}
\item You do not see the world as others see it. You see the angles between things—the gaps, the possibilities, the roads not taken.
\item You may be called to solve puzzles, to predict enemy movements, or to decipher codes that should not be decipherable.
\item You may struggle with presence. You are always a half-step ahead—or a half-step behind. The present moment is not where you live.
\item You may be asked to stop calculating—to act without prediction, to trust without knowing. The Ninth does not permit faith. It permits only angles.
\item Your shadow may move independently. You do not discuss this.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Common Quirks}

\begin{dice}
\item You count steps without noticing. Not eight—always nine. You never reach nine. You stop at eight and pause.
\item You have a habit of tilting your head when someone speaks. You are not listening to their words. You are reading the geometry of their lies.
\item You cannot stand to leave a pattern incomplete. A broken symmetry is a wound. You must fix it—or explain why not.
\item You refuse to make predictions aloud. The Ninth does not permit witnesses to betray their witness.
\end{dice}

\subsection{Sample NPC: Geometer Venn of the Fractured Mirror}

\textbf{Archetype:} Fractal Warrior

\textbf{Patron:} The Ninth

\textbf{Codex:} A broken mirror, each shard showing a different angle

\textbf{Thiasos:} A pattern-spirit that shows glimpses of the future

\textbf{Personality:} Distant, precise, weary. He has seen too many futures. He is not sure which one is happening now.

\textbf{Conflict:} A pattern he predicted twenty years ago is finally manifesting—not as he foresaw, but as he feared. He could intervene. But intervention would break the pattern. The Ninth does not permit broken patterns.

\textbf{Quote:} \textit{"I saw this moment. Not the details—the angles. The geometry was clear. Someone would have to choose. I did not see who. I did not see if I would be the one."}

\subsection{GM Guidance: Fractal Warrior Story Hooks}

\begin{itemize}
\item The Fractal Warrior sees a pattern that should not exist—a coincidence too precise, a symmetry too perfect. Something is editing reality.
\item A prediction the Fractal Warrior made years ago has come true—but not as they expected. The future is a branching tree. They saw one branch. Another branch is happening now.
\item The Fractal Warrior's broken mirror shows a face that is not theirs. The face is familiar. They cannot place it. The mirror will not explain.
\item The Fractal Warrior dreams of a number—the ninth digit of pi. It is changing. The world is being recalculated. The Ninth is recalculating. The Fractal Warrior cannot wake up.
\end{itemize}

The thread held. The water carried. That is not a Rite. That is grace.
